title: Midwife at your cervix
description:
The Midwife at your cervix (MAYC) app has been specially designed and created by a midwife to help guide you through the pregnancy journey, whether that be as a mother, partner, grandparent or loved one. MAYC is here to empower and educate whilst also being an avenue to keep track of appointments, results and questions throughout the pregnancy.

You can expect to enjoy 

•	Reading about baby’s weekly developments and how they grow in size.
•	To do list reminders to keep you on track when the baby brain kicks.
•	A guide of pregnancy symptoms and how to best manage them.
•	Weekly education to gradually learn and prepare for all things pregnancy, birth and baby. 
•	A place to store pregnancy results (E.g., bloods and genetic testing)
•	A space to keep track of all booked appointments including who, when and where they are. 
•	A spot to keep all the burning questions you may have for the midwife, GP or obstetrician and a section to document the answers for each. 
•	A portal to keep your bump photos all in one place to create a memorable collage to look through and watch baby grow! 

Want more?  

Upgrade to gain access to the very simple to use contraction timer and feeding tracker. 
The contraction timer will note the intensity, length and frequency of contractions. It removes the guess work of trying to figure out the best time to call the midwife as it tracks how far apart contractions! Once baby is born why not utilise the feeding tracker to keep an overview of your babies’ feeds including the timing and amount, they drank. 

Let the app track your journey from beginning to end and watch baby grow.
